> "\"Commander.\"\n" [Continue]
> "He nods. He has brought two cups of tea in metal mugs: he sets them down on the tabletop between us.\n" [Choices: "Take one" (0), "\"What's going on?\"" (1), "Wait" (2) -> 0]
> "I take a mug and warm my hands. It's a small gesture of friendship.\n" [Continue]
> "Enough to give me hope?\n" [Choices: "Drink" (0), "Wait" (1) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "I raise the cup to my mouth but it's too hot to drink.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Quite a difficult situation,\" Harris begins, sternly. I've seen him adopt this stiff tone of voice before, but only when talking to the brass. \"I'm sure you agree.\"\n" [Choices: "Agree" (0), "Disagree" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"Awkward,\" I reply, sipping at my tea as though we were old friends.\n" [Choices: "Watch him" (0), "Wait" (1), "Smile" (2) -> 0]
> "His face is telling me nothing. I've seen Harris broad and full of laughter. Today he is tight, as much part of the military machine as the device in Hut 5.\n" [Continue]
> "\"We need that component,\" he says.\n" [Choices: "The stolen component..." (0), "Shrug" (1) -> 0]
> "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n" [Continue]
> "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n" [Choices: "Panic" (0), "Calculate" (1), "Deny" (2) -> 0]
> "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n" [Continue]
> "\"So. Do you have it?\" Harris is wasting no time: Bletchley is his watch. \"Do you know where it is?\"\n" [Choices: "Yes" (0), "No" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 1]
> "\"I have no idea.\"\n" [Continue]
> "There's an icy silence.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Now drink your tea and talk.\"\n" [Choices: "Drink" (0), "Put the cup down" (1) -> 0]
> "I lift the cup to my lips and sip. He waits for me to swallow before speaking again.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Lapsang Souchong,\" he remarks, placing his own cup back on the table untouched. \"Such a curious flavour. It might almost not be tea at all. You might say it hides a multitude of sins. As do you. Isn't that right?\"\n" [Choices: "Agree" (0), "Disagree" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 2]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "I open my mouth to disagree, but the words I want won't come. It is like Harris has taken a screwdriver to the sides of my jaw.\n" [Continue]
> "\"I've done things,\" I beginhelplessly. \"Things I didn't want to do. I tried not to. But in the end, it felt like cutting off my own arm to resist.\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"You mean you've left yourself open,\" Harris answers. \"To pressure. Is that what you're saying?\"\n" [Choices: "Yes" (0), "No" (1), "Evade" (2) -> 2]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"We're all under pressure here.\"\n" [Continue]
> "He looks at me with pity. \"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n" [Continue]
> "He slides his thumb between two fingers.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Now they own you.\"\n" [Choices: "Agree" (0), "Disagree" (1), "Apologise" (2) -> 1]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"I can still fix this.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris shakes his head. \"You'll do nothing. This is beyond you now. You may go to prison or may go to firing squad - or we can change your name and move you somewhere where your indiscretions can't hurt you. But right now, none of that matters. What happens to you doesn't matter. All that matters is where that component is. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n" [Continue]
> "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n" [Choices: "Confess" (0), "Dissemble" (1) -> 1]
